description: After a Turks and Caicos court sentenced Bryan Hagerich to a suspended prison term for possession of ammunition, he returned to the U.S. and was greeted by big hugs from his two young children. Hagerich was on vacation with his family at the time of his arrest and says the bullets were left in his luggage accidentally. NBC News’ Marissa Parra has more.
title: Pennsylvania father detained in Turks and Caicos reunited with family after more than 100 days

description: Millions of Indians voted in the next-to-last round of a grueling national election with a combined opposition trying to rattle Prime Minister Narendra Modi’s campaign for a third-consecutive term.
title: Millions vote in India’s grueling election, with Prime Minister Modi’s party likely to win third term

description: The IDF said it was launching an investigation, after a video appeared to show a reservist calling for a mutiny against Defense Minister Yoav Gallant.
title: Israel's military probes video appearing to show reservist calling for mutiny against defense minister

description: Scientists explain the loss of the Humboldt Glacier in Venezuela's Sierra Nevada, which they believe makes the South American country the first in modern history to lose all its glaciers.
title: 'A great sadness': Venezuela is first Andean country to lose of all its glaciers

description: Forty three people who were on board a Singapore Airlines flight that hit severe turbulence remain hospitalized in Bangkok four days after the emergency, a hospital in Thailand's capital said on Saturday.
title: Dozens remain hospitalized after deadly turbulence hit Singapore Airlines flight

description: Bodies lie in the pockmarked streets, smoke billows from the ruins of homes, fences sit flattened: A new video offers a rare view inside a front-line city that has taken on the brunt of the fighting as Russia presses on with its offensive in northern Ukraine.
title: Video shows death on the streets of Ukraine town at heart of new Russian offensive

description: Amid the tail end of the climbing season on Nepal's Mount Everest, at least three people are believed to have died, according to officials and those close to the deceased.
title: At least 3 climbers believed dead on Mount Everest

description: French President Emmanuel Macron visited New Caledonia to announce that he would delay voting reform amid violence on the island. This comes after the Pacific archipelago has faced a week of deadly unrest.
title: French president delays voting reform amid deadly unrest
